name: Akemie's Castle
summary: Digital 4 operator FM oscillator featuring 6 algorithms and 2 separate voices with CV control of every parameter. Sound generated with original Yamaha IC's

name: Akemie's Taiko
summary: Digital FM drum voice featuring original Yamaha IC sound generation.

name: MCO
summary: Morphing 10-waveform wavetable oscillator with sub octave square output and sync input. Loud and clean AKM codec with 16b/48kHz resolution.

name: Pamela's New Workout
summary: Clock based modulation source with 8 outputs. Gates, envelopes, LFO's or quantized/smooth random selectable for each output.

name: Dark Matter
summary: Feedback processor made in collaboration with Casper Electronics. Input VCA has separate high/low clipping stages and envelope follower with self normalization to several parameters.

name: Warhorse
summary: Fully analog BBD-delay and Wasp-style multi-mode filter with integrated clipping distortion stage before the delay send.

name: Raverb
summary: Analog reverb with integrated VCA utilising BBD-delay chip. Post reverb clipping stage and separate outputs for wet and mix out.

name: Maths
summary: Analog computer consisting of 4 channels mixing section with individual attenuators and inverters and an output stage of OR/SUM/INV -logical functions. Channels 1 & 2 act as envelopes / lag generators with toggle cycle for LFO function.
